@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container py-4">
    <h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p class="text-muted"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> December 12, 2025</p>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to ER ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of the personal information stored within our Employee Records System. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard the data of employees and administrators who utilize our platform, consistent with our motto, "Invicta Excellentia" (Unconquered Excellence).</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>To facilitate effective human resource management, ER collects specific personal data, including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Identification:</strong> Full name, date of birth, gender, and civil status.</li>
            <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Email addresses, phone numbers, and home addresses.</li>
            <li><strong>Employment Details:</strong> Employee ID, job title, department, date of hire, and salary information.</li>
            <li><strong>System Usage Data:</strong> Login timestamps and activity logs within the system for security auditing.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>The data collected is used strictly for administrative and organizational purposes, such as:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Maintaining accurate employee records;</li>
            <li>Processing payroll and benefits (if applicable);</li>
            <li>Managing attendance and leave requests;</li>
            <li>Ensuring system security and preventing unauthorized access.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We take the security of your data seriously. We implement industry-standard security measures, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Sensitive data (such as passwords) is encrypted in our database.</li>
            <li><strong>Access Control:</strong> Access to personal data is restricted to authorized HR personnel and system administrators only.</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> We adhere to strict internal protocols to ensure data integrity.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent personal identification information to users or third parties. Data is only disclosed when:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Required by law or legal process.</li>
            <li>Necessary to protect the rights or property of the organization.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>As a user of the ER system, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access your personal record.</li>
            <li>Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
            <li>Request the deletion of your data (subject to company retention policies).</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify users of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact the System Administrator at:</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:sgt.spartan19@gmail.com">sgt.spartan19@gmail.com</a></p>
    </section>
</div>
